Program: Outlook
Title: The boy, the wish and the nuclear weapons
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csz37s
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 8 Sep 2019
In 1986 American teenager, Jeff Henigson was diagnosed with brain cancer and given two years left to live. He had just one wish: to travel to the Soviet Union, meet the country's leader Mikhail Gorbachev and attempt to broker a nuclear peace deal. Jeff has written a book about his experience called WarHead. Presenter: Asya Fouks Producer: Thomas Harding Assinder Picture: Teenager Jeff Henigson in bed after undergoing brain surgery Credit: Jeff Henigson Show less